- On Sweeney Road.

40:27.148 --> 40:29.956
Right near Spider Lake.
I'm feeling her pulse.

40:29.956 --> 40:32.256
She's definitely dead.
She's not breathing.

40:32.256 --> 40:35.513
Her neck is broken.
I don't think I... uh!

40:35.513 --> 40:37.965
Oh, God.
I can't breathe.

40:37.965 --> 40:39.392
- Sir?
- My heart!

40:39.392 --> 40:40.944
Are you all right?

40:40.944 --> 40:45.794
Imitating his father was easy. As Clara
had mentioned, you sounded just like him.

40:45.794 --> 40:47.770
So it was perfect.

40:47.770 --> 40:49.445
They were both dead.

40:49.445 --> 40:51.787
Your stepmother had obviously died first.

40:51.787 --> 40:55.075
- Who are you?
- This is my boss, Adrian Monk.

40:55.075 --> 40:58.548
Hello!
Sorry we're late.

40:58.893 --> 41:01.008
Hello, darling.

41:03.887 --> 41:08.058
Natalie?
When did this happen?

41:18.803 --> 41:21.883
- I told you I'd take care of it.
- What is it?

41:21.883 --> 41:24.356
It's from the deputy commissioner.
That's his signature.

41:24.356 --> 41:27.828
It says that you, Adrian Monk, are
exempt from the current hiring freeze,

41:27.828 --> 41:30.369
and when you are ready
to come back to work,

41:30.369 --> 41:32.687
your badge will be waiting for you.

41:33.640 --> 41:37.591
- How did you do that?
- I talked to the man. I laid it all out.

41:37.591 --> 41:39.878
- He threatened to quit.
- You did?

41:39.878 --> 41:44.389
Yeah, I was there. It was pretty intense.
And I seriously considered quitting.

41:44.389 --> 41:46.745
I wasn't bluffing.
I meant it.

41:46.745 --> 41:49.887
Me too.
You could tell I was about to consider it.

41:49.887 --> 41:53.711
- Leland, I don't know how to...
- Buy me lunch, we'll call it even.

41:53.711 --> 41:55.530
- Okay.
- What are you doing?

41:55.530 --> 41:58.410
- I was just...
- You're not my butler.

41:58.410 --> 42:00.284
- Oh, right.
- You're a cop.

